;STRUCTURE OF A T4 LYSOZYME MUTANT WITH AN ENGINEERED METAL
BINDING SITE. THIS MUTANT DESIGNATED APO-H2 IS THE PROTEIN
WHICH CONTAINS THE METAL BINDING SITE, BUT WITH NO METAL
LIGANDS. THE METAL LIGANDS ZN, CO, NI WILL BE DESCRIBED AS
SEPARATE PDB FILES AND INCLUDED IN THE PAPER "AN ADAPTABLE
METAL-BINDING SITE ENGINEERED INTO T4 LYSOZYME."
